"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT users.Id)\nFROM comments\nJOIN users ON comments.UserId = users.Id\nWHERE comments.Score = 0 AND users.Age = 40;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the distinct number of users who are 40 years old and have made comments with a score of 0. It joins the `comments` table with the `users` table using the foreign key relationship `comments.UserId = users.Id`."